Sometimes the base class exists mostly to describe what every subclass must provide.

```python
class CatalogItem:
    def __init__(self, title):
        self.title = title

    def label(self):
        raise NotImplementedError("Subclasses must define label().")
```

This says, "every catalog item should have a `label()` method."
